snippet.textDisplay: Sorry Riley but the headset from the ad spot does not have noise cancelation, took me hours to realise that... But once you think about it, it's quite logical. The headset connects to the computer via the 3.5 mm audio jack, thus it can't get power to have any noise cancelation, but because I'm not smart enough to have figured out that by myself I did contact Sennheiser, which is where I got this information. It is sad that Drop keeps on false advertising this feature, because they really do provide a good service. The person from Sennheiser that I was talking with recommended me to just return the headset, but the sound quality is actually really nice and the open back design is nice too, so I still decided to keep the headset.
